description: President Lukashenko's main rival refuses to accept defeat, as clashes continue for a second night.
title: Belarus election: Opposition disputes Lukashenko landslide win
title_page: Belarus election: Opposition disputes Lukashenko landslide win - BBC News
maintext: "So Lukashenko, who is at the top of the power structure and at the head of the state, after getting 80% of the vote must voluntarily hand over power to them," the president said. "The orders are coming from over there [abroad]."
